Show HN: Personal Drill Sergeant will keep you productive. And fit
text:
Having someone watch you work can do wonders for your focus and productivity. Pair programming, study together, people even hire assistants just for that.

So, meet Drill Sergeant - he will check up on you periodically but randomly, and if you' re caught slacking off, you will do pushups. I know this works for me, at least.

Ask HN: On the frontpage there are people who've been shut out of PayPal and FB
text:
Is there a solution to prevent all of these digital system lockouts?

There are new ones every few weeks. Or more often. Google. Stripe. Facebook. PayPal.

I'm glad that they're allowed on HN, because at least there's some visibly bought to the issue.

But we need better solutions for this.

If we have issues with governments, we can get lawyers. But if we have issues with digital governments, we need to make a post on HN and hope that an employee sees it?

Ask HN: Alternatives to Linode for running simple VPSes?
text:
What are good alternatives to Linode for running virtual private servers in 2023?

I know Digital Ocean is a good one. Are there more?

How do these alternatives look for long term viability? Linode had a good run for 20 years! Which other alternative is likely to last and provide robust service for another 20 years (think 2043!)?

Do justify your recommendations and explain why your recommended alternative is better than the others for running virtual private servers? What do they do better than others? How good is their customer support in comparison to others? Why do you think they will last for another 20 years?

Show HN: Thwarting the Theft of Credentials Using Container
text: Recent high-profile cases such as the source code leaks of Slack's GitHub repositories in January 2023, CircleCI in January 2023, and before that GitHub accounts in April 2022, and Okta in December 2022 are evidence of this trend. In this short blog, we briefly review the attack and explain how the use of online and secured Containerized Development Environments (CDEs) is a great way to protect your DevOps process and implement a robust code development infrastructure to support DevSecOps practices.
